This paper presents an algorithm for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is based on the Optimism in the Face of Uncertainty principle, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses regret bounds, which is a topic in optimization and decision making (cs.DS). The algorithm is designed to work with Markov decision processes, which are commonly used in control systems and robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of its regret bound, which is a topic in mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
